id: jf-mkzh
title: Ratchet command-layer coverage above the 59 percent baseline
description: "The July 16 modernization run established 888 passing tests and 59.26% aggregate line coverage. Core API and formatter modules are near-complete, but many Commander action callbacks are exercised only by optional live-server E2E tests and remain low-coverage in isolated CI. Add dependency-injected command harnesses in coherent slices, establish a non-regressing coverage floor, and raise it incrementally without requiring live Jellyfin credentials."
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 2
tags[4]: coverage,quality,roadmap,testing
created_at: "2026-07-16T17:00:03.971Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-16T17:00:03.971Z"
author: codex
acceptance_criteria: Record and enforce a non-regressing baseline for functions and lines.; Add isolated command tests by domain until aggregate line coverage exceeds 80 percent.; Keep changed command/formatter modules at or near 100 percent and retain read-only live E2E coverage.
goal: jf-mqpo
value: Prevent regressions in user-facing command orchestration while preserving fast isolated CI.
impact: "Makes global option propagation, validation, error formatting, and request wiring measurable across every command family."
outcome: A ratcheted repository-wide coverage policy with command modules covered by isolated tests and live E2E retained as supplemental proof.
parent: jf-mqpo
risk: medium
confidence: high
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-16T17:00:03.971Z",codex,"Baseline from bun test --coverage on 2026-07-16: 888 pass,177 credential-dependent E2E skip,44.69% functions,59.26% lines; changed session formatter 100% functions and lines."
tests[1]{command,path,scope,timeout_seconds}:
  "bun run test:coverage",package.json,project,1200
body: ""
